ands, making it the\nbrightest among the current sample of MD winds seen by XRT. We infer the\ninitial spin period ($P_0$) and the surface polar cap magnetic field strength\n($B_p$) of the magnetar as $1.02 \\times 10^{15}~{\\rm G} \\leq B_{p} \\leq 1.80\n\\times 10^{15}~{\\rm G}$ and 1~ms $\\leq P_{0}v\\leq 1.77$~ms, and the radiative\nefficiency of the wind is $\\eta_w \\geq 32\\%$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 26 Apr 2020 01:57:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-17"}
